to go to that river. Move out.

473
00:44:09,080 --> 00:44:14,916
- One, two, hup!
- Step it up! Look alive out there.

474
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:18,515
The good thing about Vietnam
is there was always someplace to go.

475
00:44:18,600 --> 00:44:20,511
Fire in the hole!

476
00:44:23,400 --> 00:44:25,789
Gump, check out that hole.

477
00:44:25,880 --> 00:44:28,678
And there was always something to do.

478
00:44:28,760 --> 00:44:31,638
Mount 'em up!
Spread out! Cover his back!

479
00:44:36,440 --> 00:44:42,310
One day it started raining,
and it didn't quit for four months.

480
00:44:42,400 --> 00:44:45,472
We've been through every
kind of rain there is.

481
00:44:45,560 --> 00:44:52,033
Little bitty stinging rain
and big old fat rain,

482
00:44:52,120 --> 00:44:56,398
rain that flew in sideways,
and sometimes rain even seemed

483
00:44:56,480 --> 00:44:59,836
to come straight up from underneath.

484
00:44:59,920 --> 00:45:03,196
Shoot, it even rained at night.

485
00:45:03,280 --> 00:45:06,078
- Hey, Forrest.
- Hey, Bubba.

486
00:45:06,160 --> 00:45:09,755
I'm going to lean up against you.
You lean up against me.

487
00:45:09,840 --> 00:45:13,913
This way we don't have to sleep
with our heads in the mud.

488
00:45:14,000 --> 00:45:16,434
You know why
we're a good partnership, Forrest?

489
00:45:16,520 --> 00:45:21,469
'Cause we be watching out for one
another, like brothers and stuff.

490
00:45:23,240 --> 00:45:26,789
Hey, Forrest,
something I been thinking about.

491
00:45:26,880 --> 00:45:29,713
I got a very important question
to ask you.

492
00:45:31,480 --> 00:45:35,075
How would you like to go
into the shrimping business with me?

493
00:45:36,680 --> 00:45:39,672
- OK.
- Man, I tell you what.

494
00:45:39,760 --> 00:45:41,955
I got it all figured out, too.

495
00:45:42,040 --> 00:45:44,838
So many pounds of shrimp
will pay off the boat.

496
00:45:44,920 --> 00:45:48,071
So many pounds for gas.
We'll live right on the boat.

497
00:45:48,160 --> 00:45:50,390
We ain't got to pay no rent.

498
00:45:50,480 --> 00:45:54,189
We can just work it together, split
everything right down the middle.

499
00:45:54,280 --> 00:45:59,274
Man, I'm telling you, 50-50. Hey,
Forrest, all the shrimp you can eat.

500
00:46:00,840 --> 00:46:03,229
That's a fine idea.

501
00:46:03,320 --> 00:46:05,959
Bubba did have a fine idea.

502
00:46:09,360 --> 00:46:12,557
I even wrote Jenny
and told her all about it.

503
00:46:12,640 --> 00:46:16,189
I sent her letters.
Not every day, but almost.

504
00:46:16,280 --> 00:46:20,796
I told her what I was doing
and asked her what she was doing,

505
00:46:20,880 --> 00:46:23,838
and told her
how I thought about her always.

506
00:46:25,200 --> 00:46:28,988
And how I was looking forward
to getting a letter from her

507
00:46:29,080 --> 00:46:31,833
just as soon as she had the time.

508
00:46:31,920 --> 00:46:34,673
I'd always let her know
that I was OK.

509
00:46:34,760 --> 00:46:41,791
Then I'd sign each letter
"Love, Forrest Gump."

510
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:58,636
This one day,
we was out walking like always,

511
00:46:58,720 --> 00:47:04,397
and then, just like that,
somebody turned off the rain,

512
00:47:04,480 --> 00:47:06,914
and the sun come out.

513
00:47:08,680 --> 00:47:12,036
Ambush! Take cover!

514
00:47:20,800 --> 00:47:25,510
- Get that pig up here, God damn it!
- Forrest, are you OK?

515
00:47:28,120 --> 00:47:30,350
Strong Arm, Strong Arm!

516
00:47:32,400 --> 00:47:37,076
- We've got a man down.
- Strong Arm, this is Leg Lima 6!

517
00:47:37,160 --> 00:47:41,836
Roger, Strong Arm! We have incoming
from the treeline at Point Blue...

518
00:47:41,920 --> 00:47:45,356
