We're getting it hard!

519
00:47:45,440 --> 00:47:49,592
- Misfire! Misfire!
- God damn it!

520
00:47:51,200 --> 00:47:54,988
Get that pig unfucked
and put it in the treeline!

521
00:47:56,680 --> 00:47:59,069
They got us down, hard and hurt.

522
00:47:59,160 --> 00:48:02,630
We're going to move back
to the blue line.

523
00:48:03,560 --> 00:48:05,437
Pull back! Pull back!

524
00:48:05,640 --> 00:48:09,315
- Forrest! Run, Forrest!
- Pull back!

525
00:48:09,400 --> 00:48:13,712
- Run! Run, man! Run!
- Pull back, Gump!

526
00:48:15,360 --> 00:48:18,193
Run, God damn it! Run!

527
00:48:43,160 --> 00:48:47,073
I ran and ran
just like Jenny told me to.

528
00:48:50,120 --> 00:48:55,672
I ran so far so fast that soon I was
all by myself, which was a bad thing.

529
00:48:59,360 --> 00:49:03,751
Bubba was my best good friend.
I had to make sure he was OK.

530
00:49:12,440 --> 00:49:14,829
Where the hell are you?

531
00:49:16,840 --> 00:49:22,472
And on my way back to find Bubba,
there was a boy laying on the ground.

532
00:49:22,560 --> 00:49:26,439
Tex. OK.

533
00:49:26,960 --> 00:49:30,669
I couldn't let him lay there
all alone, scared the way he was,

534
00:49:30,760 --> 00:49:34,116
so I grabbed him up
and run him out of there.

535
00:49:48,800 --> 00:49:51,553
Every time I went back
looking for Bubba,

536
00:49:51,640 --> 00:49:55,792
somebody else was saying,
"Help me, Forrest, help me!"

537
00:50:02,000 --> 00:50:04,150
OK. Here. Here.

538
00:50:06,480 --> 00:50:09,233
No sweat, man.
Lay back. You'll be OK.

539
