I could eat. And guess what?

586
00:54:43,320 --> 00:54:47,233
A good friend of mine was
in the bed right next door.

587
00:54:47,840 --> 00:54:52,436
Lieutenant Dan,
I got you some ice cream.

588
00:54:52,520 --> 00:54:55,478
Lieutenant Dan, ice cream!

589
00:55:06,080 --> 00:55:08,799
It's time for your bath,
Lieutenant.

590
00:55:17,040 --> 00:55:18,314
Harper!

591
00:55:21,520 --> 00:55:24,876
Cooper. Larson.

592
00:55:26,040 --> 00:55:29,828
Webster. Gump.

593
00:55:29,920 --> 00:55:32,480
- Gump!
- I'm Forrest Gump.

594
00:55:35,080 --> 00:55:39,073
Kyle. Nichols.

595
00:55:40,520 --> 00:55:44,479
McMill. Johnson.

596
00:56:00,760 --> 00:56:04,992
Gump, how can you watch
that stupid shit? Turn it off.

597
00:56:05,080 --> 00:56:07,753
You are tuned to the American Forces
Vietnam Network.

598
00:56:07,840 --> 00:56:10,115
This is Channel 6, Saigon.

599
00:56:12,760 --> 00:56:17,231
Good catch, Gump.
You know how to play this?

600
00:56:19,520 --> 00:56:22,034
Come on. Let me show you.

601
00:56:23,440 --> 00:56:27,752
The secret to this game is
no matter what happens,

602
00:56:27,840 --> 00:56:33,073
never, ever take your eye
off the ball.

603
00:56:34,680 --> 00:56:36,352
All right.

604
00:56:39,160 --> 00:56:42,994
For some reason, ping-pong
came very natural to me.

605
00:56:43,080 --> 00:56:46,277
See? Any idiot can play.

606
00:56:46,360 --> 00:56:48,635
So I started playing it all the time.

607
00:56:49,520 --> 00:56:54,548
I played ping-pong even when I didn't
have anyone to play ping-pong with.

608
00:57:02,840 --> 00:57:07,789
The hospital's people said it
made me look like a duck in water,

609
00:57:07,880 --> 00:57:09,518
whatever that means.

610
00:57:09,600 --> 00:57:12,797
Even Lieutenant Dan
would come and watch me play.

611
00:57:17,320 --> 00:57:22,553
I played ping-pong so much,
I even played it in my sleep.

612
00:57:29,280 --> 00:57:33,831
Now, you listen to me.
We all have a destiny.

613
00:57:33,920 --> 00:57:37,117
Nothing just happens.
It's all part of a plan!

614
00:57:37,200 --> 00:57:40,078
I should have died
out there with my men,

615
00:57:40,160 --> 00:57:45,109
but now, I'm nothing but
a goddamn cripple, a legless freak!

616
00:57:46,080 --> 00:57:49,117
Look. Look! Look at me!
You see that?

617
00:57:49,200 --> 00:57:52,954
Do you know what it's like
not to be able to use your legs?

618
00:57:55,640 --> 00:57:57,676
Yes, sir, I do.

619
00:58:00,960 --> 00:58:06,114
Did you hear what I said?
You cheated me! I had a destiny.

620
00:58:06,200 --> 00:58:09,875
I was supposed to die in the field
with honour!

621
00:58:10,360 --> 00:58:14,911
That was my destiny,
and you cheated me out of it!

622
00:58:22,960 --> 00:58:25,315
You understand what I'm saying, Gump?

623
00:58:28,400 --> 00:58:35,238
This wasn't supposed to happen,
not to me. I had a destiny.

624
00:58:37,320 --> 00:58:41,711
I was Lieutenant Dan Taylor.

625
00:58:46,920 --> 00:58:50,595
You're still Lieutenant Dan.

626
00:59:11,840 --> 00:59:16,311
Look at me.
What am I going to do now?

627
