Forrest, we have very different
lives, you know.

732
01:09:15,680 --> 01:09:19,116
I want you to have this.

733
01:09:23,360 --> 01:09:25,316
Forrest, I can't keep this.

734
01:09:27,200 --> 01:09:31,830
I got it just by doing
what you told me to do.

735
01:09:33,320 --> 01:09:37,916
- Why are you so good to me?
- You're my girl.

736
01:09:40,400 --> 01:09:42,630
I'll always be your girl.

737
01:10:20,080 --> 01:10:25,438
And just like that,
she was gone out of my life again.

738
01:10:27,200 --> 01:10:34,151
It's one small step for man,
one giant leap for mankind.

739
01:10:38,560 --> 01:10:42,917
I thought I was going back
to Vietnam, but instead they decided

740
01:10:43,000 --> 01:10:47,073
the best way for me to fight
the communists was to play ping-pong,

741
01:10:47,160 --> 01:10:50,755
so I was in the Special Services,
travelling around the country,

742
01:10:50,840 --> 01:10:54,753
cheering up wounded veterans and
showing 'em how to play ping-pong.

743
01:10:54,840 --> 01:10:56,353
I was so good,

744
01:10:56,440 --> 01:10:59,716
the Army decided I should be
on the All-American ping-pong team.

745
01:11:00,680 --> 01:11:03,956
We were the first Americans
to visit the land of China

746
01:11:04,040 --> 01:11:05,871
in a million years or something.

747
01:11:05,960 --> 01:11:08,758
Somebody said world peace
was in our hands,

748
01:11:08,840 --> 01:11:11,354
but all I did was play ping-pong.

749
01:11:11,440 --> 01:11:14,876
When I got home,
I was a national celebrity,

750
01:11:14,960 --> 01:11:17,793
famouser even than Captain Kangaroo.

751
01:11:17,880 --> 01:11:21,111
Here he is, Forrest Gump. Right here.

752
01:11:29,640 --> 01:11:34,077
- Forrest Gump, John Lennon.
- Welcome home.

753
01:11:34,160 --> 01:11:38,199
Can you tell us, what was China like?

754
