Now, that's Lieutenant Dan.

764
01:12:26,920 --> 01:12:28,672
Lieutenant Dan!

765
01:12:28,760 --> 01:12:33,550
They gave you
the Congressional Medal of Honour.

766
01:12:34,600 --> 01:12:36,397
Yes, sir. They surely did.

767
01:12:36,480 --> 01:12:41,793
They gave you, an imbecile,
a moron who goes on television

768
01:12:41,880 --> 01:12:47,000
and makes a fool out of himself
in front of the whole damn country,

769
01:12:47,080 --> 01:12:49,435
the Congressional Medal of Honour.

770
01:12:50,040 --> 01:12:51,792
Yes, sir.

771
01:12:53,760 --> 01:12:56,877
Well, that's just perfect!

772
01:12:58,280 --> 01:13:03,308
Well, I just got one thing to say
to that. Goddamn bless America.

773
01:13:11,560 --> 01:13:13,312
Lieutenant Dan!

774
01:13:13,400 --> 01:13:16,836
Lieutenant Dan
said he was living in a hotel.

775
01:13:16,920 --> 01:13:21,914
Because he didn't have no legs, he
spent his time exercising his arms.

776
01:13:24,040 --> 01:13:25,871
Take a right. Take a right!

777
01:13:29,440 --> 01:13:31,192
Come on, already!

778
01:13:31,280 --> 01:13:34,511
What do you do here in New York,
Lieutenant Dan?

779
01:13:34,600 --> 01:13:36,830
I'm living off the government tit.

780
01:13:41,200 --> 01:13:45,478
Are you blind? I'm walking here!
Get out! Come on. Go, go, go!

781
01:13:52,280 --> 01:13:56,512
I stayed with Lieutenant Dan
and celebrated the holidays.

782
01:14:00,240 --> 01:14:04,631
You have a great year,
and hurry home. God bless you.

783
01:14:06,720 --> 01:14:09,837
Have you found Jesus yet, Gump?

784
01:14:09,920 --> 01:14:13,913
