Jesus this and Jesus that.
Have I found Jesus?

787
01:14:34,880 --> 01:14:38,156
They even had a priest
come and talk to me.

788
01:14:38,240 --> 01:14:43,633
He said God is listening,
but I have to help myself.

789
01:14:43,720 --> 01:14:46,473
Now, if I accept Jesus into my heart,

790
01:14:46,560 --> 01:14:50,712
I'll get to walk beside him
in the kingdom of heaven.

791
01:14:50,800 --> 01:14:53,030
Did you hear what I said?

792
01:14:54,280 --> 01:14:58,432
Walk beside him
in the kingdom of heaven.

793
01:14:58,520 --> 01:15:04,550
Well, kiss my crippled ass. God
is listening? What a crock of shit.

794
01:15:07,720 --> 01:15:10,075
I'm going to heaven, Lieutenant Dan.

795
01:15:17,640 --> 01:15:18,959
Well...

796
01:15:21,520 --> 01:15:25,274
Before you go, why don't you
get your ass down to the corner

797
01:15:25,360 --> 01:15:28,033
- and get us more ripple?
- Yes, sir.

798
01:15:28,120 --> 01:15:32,193
We're at approximately 45th street
in New York City at One Astor Plaza.

799
01:15:32,280 --> 01:15:34,475
This is the site
of the old Astor Hotel...

800
01:15:34,560 --> 01:15:38,348
- What the hell is in Bayou La Batre?
- Shrimping boats.

801
01:15:38,440 --> 01:15:41,557
Shrimping boats? Who gives a shit
about shrimping boats?

802
01:15:41,640 --> 01:15:45,428
I got to buy me one
soon as I have some money.

803
01:15:45,520 --> 01:15:46,953
I promised Bubba in Vietnam

804
01:15:47,040 --> 01:15:50,191
that as soon as the war was over,
we'd be partners.

805
01:15:50,280 --> 01:15:53,670
He'd be the captain
and I'd be his first mate.

806
01:15:53,760 --> 01:15:56,513
But now that he's dead,
I got to be the captain.

807
01:15:56,600 --> 01:15:58,431
A shrimp boat captain.

808
01:15:58,520 --> 01:16:01,557
Yes, sir. A promise is a promise,
Lieutenant Dan.

809
01:16:03,680 --> 01:16:05,557
Now hear this!

810
01:16:06,920 --> 01:16:11,198
Private Gump here is gonna be
a shrimp boat captain.

811
01:16:11,280 --> 01:16:14,989
Tell you what, Gilligan. The day
you are a shrimp boat captain,

812
01:16:15,080 --> 01:16:17,230
I will come and be your first mate.

813
01:16:18,640 --> 01:16:23,395
If you're ever a shrimp boat captain,
that's the day I'm an astronaut!

814
01:16:23,480 --> 01:16:26,631
Danny, what are you complaining
about? How you doing?

815
01:16:26,720 --> 01:16:32,033
- Mr Hot Wheels. Who's your friend?
- My name is Forrest. Forrest Gump.

816
01:16:32,120 --> 01:16:36,272
This is Cunning Carla
and Long-limbs Lenore.

817
01:16:36,360 --> 01:16:40,069
So where you been, babycakes?
Haven't seen you around lately.

818
01:16:40,160 --> 01:16:42,549
You should have been here
for Christmas,

819
01:16:42,640 --> 01:16:46,394
'cause Tommy bought a free round
and gave everybody a turkey sandwich.

820
01:16:46,480 --> 01:16:48,277
Well, I had company.

821
01:16:48,400 --> 01:16:52,154
We was just there!
That's Times Square.

822
01:16:52,240 --> 01:16:56,950
Don't you just love New Year's?
You can start all over.

823
01:16:57,040 --> 01:16:59,634
Everybody gets a second chance.

824
01:17:00,160 --> 01:17:02,958
It's funny,
but in the middle of all that fun,

825
01:17:03,040 --> 01:17:04,951
I began to think about Jenny,

826
01:17:05,040 --> 01:17:09,477
wondering how she was spending her
New Year's night out in California.

827
01:17:30,880 --> 01:17:34,270
Nine, eight, seven, six,

828
01:17:34,360 --> 01:17:40,230
five, four, three, two, one!
Happy New Year!

829
01:17:56,800 --> 01:17:59,598
Happy New Year, Lieutenant Dan!

830
01:18:32,840 --> 01:18:36,594
What are you, stupid or something?
What's your problem?

831
01:18:36,680 --> 01:18:41,435
What's his problem? Did you lose
your packet in the war or something?

832
01:18:41,520 --> 01:18:44,273
- Is your friend stupid or something?
- What did you say?

833
01:18:44,360 --> 01:18:46,590
I said is your friend
stupid or something?

834
01:18:46,680 --> 01:18:49,433
- Don't call him stupid!
- Hey, don't push her!

835
01:18:49,520 --> 01:18:52,353
You shut up!
Don't you ever call him stupid!

836
01:18:52,440 --> 01:18:54,670
Why you so upset?

837
01:18:54,760 --> 01:18:58,150
Get your goddamn clothes
and get the hell out of here!

838
01:18:58,240 --> 01:19:01,277
You should be in a sideshow.
You're so pathetic!

839
01:19:01,360 --> 01:19:02,759
Get out of here!

840
01:19:02,840 --> 01:19:06,196
- You retard!
- Loser. You freak!

841
01:19:10,560 --> 01:19:12,312
Oh, no.

842
01:19:36,080 --> 01:19:40,232
I'm sorry I ruined your New Year's
Eve party, Lieutenant Dan.

843
01:19:40,320 --> 01:19:42,595
She tastes like cigarettes.

844
01:19:58,120 --> 01:20:02,716
I guess Lieutenant Dan figured
there's some things you can't change.

845
01:20:02,800 --> 01:20:05,633
He didn't want to be called crippled

846
01:20:05,720 --> 01:20:09,030
like I didn't want
to be called stupid.

847
01:20:12,880 --> 01:20:15,030
Happy New Year, Gump.

848
01:20:20,000 --> 01:20:22,389
The U.S. Ping-pong team met
with President Nixon today...

849
01:20:22,480 --> 01:20:25,836
Wouldn't you know it?
A few months later,

850
01:20:25,920 --> 01:20:30,072
they invited me and the ping-pong
team to visit the White House.

851
01:20:30,160 --> 01:20:33,038
So I went, again.

852
01:20:33,120 --> 01:20:36,556
And I met the President
of the United States again.

853
01:20:36,640 --> 01:20:40,633
Only this time, they didn't get us
rooms in a real fancy hotel.

854
01:20:40,720 --> 01:20:44,076
Are you enjoying yourself
in our nation's capital, young man?

855
01:20:44,160 --> 01:20:47,197
- Where are you staying?
- It's called the Hotel Ebbott.

856
01:20:47,280 --> 01:20:49,714
Oh, no. I know a much nicer hotel.

857
01:20:49,800 --> 01:20:53,952
It's brand-new. Very modern.
I'll have my people take care of it.

858
01:20:54,040 --> 01:20:56,554
- Security.
- Yeah. Sir...

859
01:20:56,640 --> 01:21:01,760
You might want to send a maintenance
man to that office across the way.

860
01:21:01,840 --> 01:21:06,118
The lights are off and they must be
looking for a fuse box,

861
01:21:06,200 --> 01:21:09,033
'cause them flashlights,
they're keeping me awake.

862
01:21:09,120 --> 01:21:12,635
- OK, sir. I'll check it out.
- Thank you. Good night.

863
01:21:15,240 --> 01:21:18,596
Therefore,
I shall resign the presidency

864
01:21:18,680 --> 01:21:22,832
effective at noon tomorrow.
Vice President Ford

865
01:21:22,920 --> 01:21:27,550
will be sworn in as President
at that hour in this office.

866
01:21:38,240 --> 01:21:41,073
- Forrest Gump.
- Yes, sir!

867
01:21:41,160 --> 01:21:46,757
As you were. I have your
discharge papers. Service is up, son.

868
01:21:48,440 --> 01:21:51,637
Does this mean
I can't play ping-pong no more?

869
01:21:51,720 --> 01:21:53,631
For the Army, it does.

870
01:21:55,520 --> 01:22:00,833
And just like that, my service
in the United States Army was over.

871
01:22:05,120 --> 01:22:07,031
So I went home.

872
01:22:27,920 --> 01:22:31,799
- I'm home, Mama.
- I know. I know.

873
01:22:33,120 --> 01:22:34,553
Louise, he's here.

874
01:22:34,640 --> 01:22:38,553
When I got home, I had no idea,
but Mama'd had all sorts of visitors.

875
01:22:38,640 --> 01:22:41,200
We've had all sorts of visitors.

876
01:22:41,280 --> 01:22:43,919
Everybody wants you to use
their ping-pong stuff.

877
01:22:44,000 --> 01:22:47,549
One man even left a check for $25,000

878
01:22:47,640 --> 01:22:51,269
if you'd be agreeable to saying
you like using their paddle.

879
01:22:51,360 --> 01:22:53,669
I only like using my own paddle.

880
01:22:53,760 --> 01:22:55,796
- Hi, Miss Louise.
- Hey, Forrest.

881
01:22:55,880 --> 01:22:59,509
I know that,
but it's $25,000, Forrest.

882
01:22:59,600 --> 01:23:02,797
I thought maybe
you could hold it for a while,

883
01:23:02,880 --> 01:23:05,269
see if it grows on you.

884
01:23:05,360 --> 01:23:09,751
That Mama, she sure was right.
It's funny how things work out.

885
01:23:09,840 --> 01:23:11,751
I didn't stay home for long

886
01:23:11,840 --> 01:23:16,595
because I'd made a promise to Bubba,
and I always try to keep my promise,

887
01:23:16,680 --> 01:23:20,389
so I went on down to Bayou La Batre
to meet Bubba's family.

888
01:23:20,480 --> 01:23:24,758
Are you crazy or just plain stupid?

889
01:23:24,840 --> 01:23:28,753
- Stupid is as stupid does, Mrs Blue.
- I guess.

890
01:23:28,920 --> 01:23:33,357
And, of course,
I paid my respect to Bubba himself.

891
01:23:34,480 --> 01:23:37,074
Hey, Bubba. It's me, Forrest Gump.

892
01:23:40,200 --> 01:23:44,955
I remember everything you said,
and I got it all figured out.

893
01:23:46,680 --> 01:23:54,030
I'm taking $24,562.47 that I got,

894
01:23:54,120 --> 01:23:57,396
that's left after a new haircut
and a new suit

895
01:23:57,480 --> 01:24:00,313
and I took Mama out
to a real fancy dinner,

896
01:24:00,400 --> 01:24:03,153
and I bought a bus ticket,
and three Dr Peppers.

897
01:24:03,240 --> 01:24:07,552
Tell me something.
Are you stupid or something?

898
01:24:07,640 --> 01:24:10,108
Stupid is as stupid does, sir.

899
01:24:10,200 --> 01:24:11,997
That's what's left after me saying,

900
01:24:12,080 --> 01:24:15,868
"When I was in China
on the All-America ping-pong team,

901
01:24:15,960 --> 01:24:17,757
"I just loved playing ping-pong

902
01:24:17,840 --> 01:24:19,910
"with my Flex-o-lite
ping-pong paddle,"

903
01:24:20,000 --> 01:24:21,956
which everybody knows isn't true,

904
01:24:22,040 --> 01:24:25,953
but Mama said it was just a little
white lie, it wasn't hurting nobody.

905
01:24:26,040 --> 01:24:30,079
So anyway,
I'm putting all that on gas, ropes,

906
01:24:30,160 --> 01:24:34,153
and new nets
and a brand-new shrimping boat.

907
01:24:54,560 --> 01:24:57,757
Bubba told me everything
he knew about shrimping,

908
01:24:57,840 --> 01:25:00,638
but you know what I found out?

909
01:25:01,680 --> 01:25:04,240
Shrimping is tough.

910
01:25:06,080 --> 01:25:08,640
I only caught five.

911
01:25:08,720 --> 01:25:12,076
A couple more,
you can have yourself a cocktail.

912
01:25:13,720 --> 01:25:16,553
You ever think about
naming this old boat?

913
01:25:16,640 --> 01:25:19,393
It's bad luck
to have a boat without a name.

914
01:25:19,480 --> 01:25:21,710
I'd never named a boat before,

915
01:25:21,800 --> 01:25:26,635
but there was only one
I could think of,

916
01:25:26,720 --> 01:25:30,508
the most beautiful name
in the wide world.

917
01:25:50,800 --> 01:25:56,352
I hadn't heard from Jenny in a long
while, but I thought about her a lot.

918
01:25:56,440 --> 01:25:59,238
I hoped whatever she was doing
made her happy.

919
01:27:41,040 --> 01:27:44,237
I thought about Jenny all the time.

920
01:28:31,160 --> 01:28:35,676
Lieutenant Dan,
what are you doing here?

921
01:28:35,760 --> 01:28:38,752
Well, thought I'd try out
my sea legs.

922
01:28:38,840 --> 01:28:41,752
Well, you ain't got no legs,
Lieutenant Dan.

923
01:28:41,840 --> 01:28:47,233
Yes, I know that.
You wrote me a letter, you idiot.

924
01:28:47,320 --> 01:28:52,474
Well, well. Captain Forrest Gump.
I had to see this for myself.

925
01:28:53,760 --> 01:28:59,471
And I told you if you were
ever a shrimp boat captain,

926
01:28:59,560 --> 01:29:02,870
that I'd be your first mate.
Well, here I am.

927
01:29:02,960 --> 01:29:05,872
- I'm a man of my word.
- OK.

928
01:29:05,960 --> 01:29:09,794
But don't you be thinking that
I'm going to be calling you "Sir."

929
01:29:09,880 --> 01:29:11,950
No, sir.

930
01:29:19,720 --> 01:29:21,790
That's my boat.

931
01:29:24,200 --> 01:29:28,079
I have a feeling if we head due east,

932
01:29:28,160 --> 01:29:31,630
we'll find some shrimp.
So take a left.

933
01:29:33,040 --> 01:29:35,235
- Take a left!
- Which way?

934
01:29:35,320 --> 01:29:37,754
Over there! They're over there!

935
01:29:37,840 --> 01:29:42,470
- Get on the wheel and take a left.
- OK.

936
01:29:43,800 --> 01:29:48,032
Gump, what are you doing?
Take a left! Left!

937
01:29:49,800 --> 01:29:53,713
That's where we're going
to find those shrimp, my boy!

938
01:29:54,600 --> 01:29:56,511
That's where we'll find them.

939
01:30:08,600 --> 01:30:12,354
- Still no shrimp, Lieutenant Dan.
- OK, so I was wrong.

940
01:30:12,440 --> 01:30:15,238
How are we going to find them?

941
01:30:15,320 --> 01:30:18,949
Maybe you should
just pray for shrimp.

942
01:30:25,080 --> 01:30:27,514
So I went to church every Sunday.

943
01:30:28,960 --> 01:30:34,478
Sometimes Lieutenant Dan came too,
though he left the praying up to me.

944
01:30:48,560 --> 01:30:53,680
- No shrimp.
- Where the hell's this God of yours?

945
01:30:53,760 --> 01:30:58,595
It's funny Lieutenant Dan said that,
'cause right then God showed up.

946
01:31:14,840 --> 01:31:17,229
You'll never sink this boat!

947
01:31:17,320 --> 01:31:23,190
Now, me, I was scared,
but Lieutenant Dan, he was mad.

948
01:31:23,280 --> 01:31:25,589
Come on!

949
01:31:27,480 --> 01:31:33,112
You call this a storm?
Come on, you son of a bitch!

950
01:31:34,880 --> 01:31:42,070
It's time for a showdown! You and me!
I'm right here! Come and get me!

951
01:31:44,240 --> 01:31:47,869
You'll never sink this boat!

952
01:31:50,040 --> 01:31:51,996
Hurricane Carmen
came through here yesterday,

953
01:31:52,080 --> 01:31:54,150
destroying nearly everything
in its path.

954
01:31:54,240 --> 01:31:57,038
And as in other towns
up and down the coast,

955
01:31:57,120 --> 01:31:59,554
Bayou La Batre's
entire shrimping industry

956
01:31:59,640 --> 01:32:04,634
has fallen victim to Carmen
and has been left in utter ruin.

957
01:32:04,720 --> 01:32:06,233
This reporter has learned,

958
01:32:06,320 --> 01:32:09,995
in fact, only one shrimping boat
actually survived the storm.

959
01:32:10,080 --> 01:32:12,435
Louise. Louise, there's Forrest.

960
01:32:12,520 --> 01:32:15,478
After that, shrimping was easy.

961
01:32:21,040 --> 01:32:23,918
Since people still needed
them shrimps for shrimp cocktails

962
01:32:24,000 --> 01:32:28,152
and barbecues and all, and we were
the only boat left standing,

963
01:32:28,240 --> 01:32:33,394
Bubba-Gump shrimp's what they got.
We got a whole bunch of boats.

964
01:32:33,480 --> 01:32:35,471
Twelve Jennys, big old warehouse.

965
01:32:35,560 --> 01:32:39,678
We even have hats
that say "Bubba-Gump" on them.

966
01:32:39,760 --> 01:32:42,274
Bubba-Gump Shrimp. A household name.

967
01:32:42,360 --> 01:32:44,032
Hold on there, boy.

968
01:32:44,120 --> 01:32:48,636
Are you telling me you're the owner
of the Bubba-Gump Shrimp Corporation?

969
01:32:48,720 --> 01:32:51,518
Yes. We got more money
than Davy Crockett.

970
01:32:51,600 --> 01:32:56,628
Boy, I heard some whoppers
in my time, but that tops them all.

971
01:32:59,120 --> 01:33:02,476
We were sitting
next to a millionaire.

972
01:33:05,320 --> 01:33:10,235
Well, I thought it was
a very lovely story,

973
01:33:10,320 --> 01:33:15,235
and you tell it so well,
with such enthusiasm.

974
01:33:15,320 --> 01:33:19,154
Would you like to see
what Lieutenant Dan looks like?

975
01:33:19,240 --> 01:33:21,470
Yes, I would.

976
01:33:25,600 --> 01:33:27,352
That's him right there.

977
01:33:29,360 --> 01:33:32,158
Let me tell you something
about Lieutenant Dan.

978
01:33:38,600 --> 01:33:42,673
I never thanked you
for saving my life.

979
01:34:07,320 --> 01:34:13,350
He never actually said so, but
I think he made his peace with God.

980
01:34:20,880 --> 01:34:22,632
For the second time in 17 days,

981
01:34:22,720 --> 01:34:26,156
President Ford escaped
possible assassination today.

982
01:34:26,240 --> 01:34:30,677
- Base to Jenny 1. Base to Jenny 1.
- Jenny 1. Go, Margo.

983
01:34:30,760 --> 01:34:32,591
Forrest has a phone call.

984
01:34:32,680 --> 01:34:35,069
Well, you'll have to tell them
to call him back.

985
01:34:35,160 --> 01:34:39,517
- He is indisposed at the moment.
- His mama's sick.

986
01:34:57,480 --> 01:35:00,517
- Where's Mama?
- She's upstairs.

987
01:35:02,480 --> 01:35:04,550
Hi, Forrest.

988
01:35:04,640 --> 01:35:08,076
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- All right.

989
01:35:14,280 --> 01:35:17,795
Sure got you straightened out,
didn't we, boy?

990
01:35:28,640 --> 01:35:32,758
- What's the matter, Mama?
- I'm dying, Forrest.

991
01:35:35,080 --> 01:35:37,878
Come on in, sit down over here.

992
01:35:50,920 --> 01:35:57,268
- Why are you dying, Mama?
- It's my time. It's just my time.

993
01:35:59,080 --> 01:36:03,119
Now, don't you be afraid, sweetheart.

994
01:36:04,800 --> 01:36:09,749
Death is just a part of life.
Something we're all destined to do.

995
01:36:10,920 --> 01:36:15,994
I didn't know it,
but I was destined to be your mama.

996
01:36:16,080 --> 01:36:20,551
- I did the best I could.
- You did good.

997
01:36:20,640 --> 01:36:26,317
Well, I happen to believe
you make your own destiny.

998
01:36:26,760 --> 01:36:31,151
You have to do the best
with what God gave you.

999
01:36:34,480 --> 01:36:36,994
What's my destiny, Mama?

1000
01:36:37,080 --> 01:36:41,358
You're going to have
to figure that out for yourself.

1001
01:36:42,640 --> 01:36:45,473
Life is a box of chocolates, Forrest.

1002
01:36:45,560 --> 01:36:48,313
You never know
what you're going to get.

1003
01:36:48,400 --> 01:36:52,473
Mama always had a way of explaining
things so I could understand them.

1004
01:36:52,560 --> 01:36:54,516
I will miss you, Forrest.

1005
01:36:56,120 --> 01:37:00,238
She had got the cancer
and died on a Tuesday.

1006
01:37:00,320 --> 01:37:04,836
I bought her a new hat
with little flowers on it.

1007
01:37:07,800 --> 01:37:10,792
And that's all
I have to say about that.

1008
01:37:17,200 --> 01:37:19,953
Didn't you say you were waiting
for the number seven bus?

1009
01:37:20,040 --> 01:37:23,112
There'll be another one
along shortly.

1010
01:37:25,880 --> 01:37:30,158
Now, because I had been
a football star and war hero

1011
01:37:30,240 --> 01:37:33,073
and national celebrity
and a shrimping boat captain

1012
01:37:33,160 --> 01:37:36,869
and a college graduate, the city
fathers of Greenbow, Alabama,

1013
01:37:36,960 --> 01:37:39,554
decided to get together
and offered me a fine job.

1014
01:37:41,120 --> 01:37:44,192
So I never went back
to work for Lieutenant Dan,

1015
01:37:44,280 --> 01:37:46,953
though he did take care
of my Bubba-Gump money.

1016
01:37:47,040 --> 01:37:51,272
He got me invested
in some kind of fruit company.

1017
01:37:51,360 --> 01:37:54,875
I got a call from him saying we don't
have to worry about money no more,

1018
01:37:54,960 --> 01:37:59,158
and I said,
"That's good. One less thing."

1019
01:38:01,040 --> 01:38:04,999
Now Mama said there's only
so much fortune a man really needs,

1020
01:38:05,080 --> 01:38:08,311
and the rest is just for showing off.

1021
01:38:08,400 --> 01:38:13,713
So I gave a whole bunch of it
to the Foursquare Gospel Church.

1022
01:38:14,440 --> 01:38:19,275
And I gave a whole bunch to the
Bayou La Batre fishing hospital.

1023
01:38:20,720 --> 01:38:26,317
And even though Bubba was dead
and Lieutenant Dan said I was nuts,

1024
01:38:26,400 --> 01:38:30,075
I gave Bubba's mama Bubba's share.

1025
01:38:32,320 --> 01:38:33,912
You know what?

1026
01:38:34,000 --> 01:38:37,834
She didn't have to work
in nobody's kitchen no more.

1027
01:38:37,920 --> 01:38:40,309
That smells wonderful.

1028
01:38:40,400 --> 01:38:45,520
And 'cause I was a gozillionaire
and I liked doing it so much,

1029
01:38:45,600 --> 01:38:47,670
I cut that grass for free.

1030
01:38:50,240 --> 01:38:53,630
But at night-time
when there was nothing to do

1031
01:38:53,720 --> 01:38:58,555
and the house was all empty,
I'd always think of Jenny.

1032
01:39:59,880 --> 01:40:03,190
And then, she was there.

1033
01:40:34,880 --> 01:40:38,475
- Hello, Forrest.
- Hello, Jenny.

1034
01:40:48,800 --> 01:40:51,758
Jenny came back and stayed with me.

1035
01:40:51,840 --> 01:40:56,470
Maybe it was because
she had nowhere else to go,

1036
01:40:56,560 --> 01:41:00,348
or maybe it was because she was
so tired, 'cause she went to bed

1037
01:41:00,440 --> 01:41:04,877
and slept and slept,
like she hadn't slept in years.

1038
01:41:05,560 --> 01:41:07,676
It was wonderful having her home.

1039
01:41:07,760 --> 01:41:14,029
Every day we'd take a walk, and I'd
jabber on like a monkey in a tree,

1040
01:41:14,120 --> 01:41:16,873
and she'd listen about
ping-ponging and shrimping

1041
01:41:16,960 --> 01:41:20,748
and Mama making a trip up to heaven.
I did all the talking.

1042
01:41:20,840 --> 01:41:24,116
Jenny most of the time
was real quiet.

1043
01:42:02,080 --> 01:42:04,833
How could you do this?

1044
01:42:40,440 --> 01:42:44,797
Sometimes I guess there
just aren't enough rocks.

1045
01:42:44,880 --> 01:42:50,512
I never really knew
why she came back, but I didn't care.

1046
01:42:50,600 --> 01:42:55,151
It was like olden times.
We was like peas and carrots again.

1047
01:42:56,520 --> 01:43:00,479
Every day, I'd pick pretty flowers
and put them in her room for her,

1048
01:43:02,640 --> 01:43:06,997
and she gave me the best gift anyone
could ever get in the wide world.

1049
01:43:07,080 --> 01:43:09,036
They're just for running.

1050
01:43:12,600 --> 01:43:15,637
And she even showed me how to dance.

1051
01:43:25,120 --> 01:43:29,033
Well, we was like family,
Jenny and me...

1052
01:43:31,800 --> 01:43:34,997
and it was the happiest time
in my life.

1053
01:43:58,280 --> 01:44:02,159
You done watching it?
I'm going to bed.

1054
01:44:12,600 --> 01:44:14,830
Will you marry me?

1055
01:44:18,840 --> 01:44:22,116
I'd make a good husband, Jenny.

1056
01:44:24,600 --> 01:44:26,477
You would, Forrest.

1057
01:44:28,360 --> 01:44:30,510
But you won't marry me.

1058
01:44:32,360 --> 01:44:35,079
You don't want to marry me.

1059
01:44:38,040 --> 01:44:40,349
Why don't you love me, Jenny?

1060
01:44:45,360 --> 01:44:51,037
I'm not a smart man,
but I know what love is.

1061
01:45:30,120 --> 01:45:32,953
Forrest, I do love you.

1062
01:46:22,920 --> 01:46:28,153
- Where are you running off to?
- I'm not running.

1063
01:47:55,040 --> 01:48:00,398
That day, for no particular reason,
I decided to go for a little run.

1064
01:48:00,800 --> 01:48:04,429
So I ran to the end of the road,
and when I got there

1065
01:48:04,520 --> 01:48:07,080
I thought maybe I'd run
to the end of town.

1066
01:48:07,160 --> 01:48:09,879
President Carter,
suffering from heat exhaustion...

1067
01:48:09,960 --> 01:48:11,678
And when I got there,

1068
01:48:11,760 --> 01:48:15,753
I thought maybe I'd just
run across Greenbow County.

1069
01:48:15,840 --> 01:48:18,229
Now, thinking since I'd run this far,

1070
01:48:18,320 --> 01:48:21,995
maybe I'd just run across
the great state of Alabama.

1071
01:48:22,080 --> 01:48:25,595
And that's what I did.
I ran clear across Alabama.

1072
01:48:25,680 --> 01:48:29,195
No particular reason.
I just kept on going.

1073
01:48:29,920 --> 01:48:31,911
I ran clear to the ocean.

1074
01:48:37,240 --> 01:48:41,199
And when I got there,
I figured since I'd gone this far,

1075
01:48:41,280 --> 01:48:44,352
might as well turn around,
just keep on going.

1076
01:48:47,720 --> 01:48:51,952
And when I got to another ocean,
I figured since I'd gone this far,

1077
01:48:53,960 --> 01:48:57,396
I might as well just turn back
and keep right on going.

1078
01:48:57,480 --> 01:49:02,759
When I got tired, I slept.
When I got hungry, I ate.

1079
01:49:02,840 --> 01:49:08,233
When I had to go...
you know... I went.

1080
01:49:08,760 --> 01:49:13,993
- And so, you just ran.
- Yeah.

1081
01:49:48,320 --> 01:49:53,952
I'd think a lot about Mama
and Bubba and Lieutenant Dan.

1082
01:49:54,040 --> 01:49:59,990
But most of all, I thought about
Jenny. I thought about her a lot.

1083
01:50:01,600 --> 01:50:05,149
For more than two years,
a man named Forrest Gump,

1084
01:50:05,240 --> 01:50:07,800
a gardener from Greenbow, Alabama,
stopping only to sleep,

1085
01:50:07,880 --> 01:50:12,112
has been running across America.
Charles Cooper reports.

1086
01:50:12,200 --> 01:50:15,317
For the fourth time
on his journey across America,

1087
01:50:15,400 --> 01:50:19,996
Forrest Gump the gardener will cross
the Mississippi River again today.

1088
01:50:21,360 --> 01:50:24,750
- I'll be damned. Forrest?
- Why are you running?

1089
01:50:24,840 --> 01:50:28,230
- Are you doing this for world peace?
- For the homeless?

1090
01:50:28,320 --> 01:50:31,118
- Are you running for women's rights?
- The environment?

1091
01:50:31,200 --> 01:50:35,910
They couldn't believe somebody would
do all that running for no reason.

1092
01:50:36,000 --> 01:50:40,118
- Why are you doing this?
- I just felt like running.

1093
01:50:40,200 --> 01:50:41,713
I just felt like runnin'.

1094
01:50:42,920 --> 01:50:46,230
It's you.
I can't believe it's really you.

1095
01:50:46,320 --> 01:50:51,599
For some reason, what I was doing
seemed to make sense to people.

1096
01:50:51,680 --> 01:50:53,989
It was like an alarm
went off in my head.

1097
01:50:54,080 --> 01:50:57,550
I said, "Here's a guy
that's got his act together.

1098
01:50:57,640 --> 01:51:01,394
"Here's somebody who has the answer."
I'll follow you anywhere, Mr Gump.

1099
01:51:01,480 --> 01:51:03,675
So I got company.

1100
01:51:05,160 --> 01:51:10,951
And after that, I got more company.
And then, even more people joined in.

1101
01:51:13,040 --> 01:51:16,032
Somebody later told me
it gave people hope.

1102
01:51:19,360 --> 01:51:21,316
I don't know anything about that,

1103
01:51:21,400 --> 01:51:25,757
but some of those people asked me
if I could help them out.

1104
01:51:25,840 --> 01:51:30,152
I was wondering if you might help me.
I'm in the bumper sticker business.

1105
01:51:30,240 --> 01:51:33,596
I need a good slogan, and since
you've been so inspirational,

1106
01:51:33,680 --> 01:51:36,114
I thought
you might be able to help me...

1107
01:51:36,200 --> 01:51:40,193
Whoa, man! You just ran
through a big pile of dog shit!

1108
01:51:41,400 --> 01:51:45,279
- It happens.
- What, shit?

1109
01:51:45,360 --> 01:51:47,112
Sometimes.

1110
01:51:48,880 --> 01:51:52,236
And some years later, I heard
that that fella did come up

1111
01:51:52,320 --> 01:51:56,552
with a bumper sticker slogan
and made a lot of money off of it.

1112
01:51:56,640 --> 01:51:58,835
Another time, I was running along,

1113
01:51:58,920 --> 01:52:01,559
somebody who'd lost all his money
in the t-shirt business,

1114
01:52:01,640 --> 01:52:04,837
he wanted to put my face
on a t-shirt,

1115
01:52:04,920 --> 01:52:08,674
but he couldn't draw that well,
and he didn't have a camera.

1116
01:52:08,760 --> 01:52:12,150
Here, use this one.
Nobody likes that colour anyway.

1117
01:52:16,120 --> 01:52:17,872
Have a nice day.

1118
01:52:19,600 --> 01:52:22,876
Some years later,
I found out that that man did come up

1119
01:52:22,960 --> 01:52:26,748
with an idea for a t-shirt.
He made a lot of money.

1120
01:52:29,160 --> 01:52:33,870
Anyway, like I was saying,
I had a lot of company.

1121
01:52:33,960 --> 01:52:40,229
Mama always said, "Put the past
behind you before you can move on."

1122
01:52:40,680 --> 01:52:44,434
And I think
that's what my running was all about.

1123
01:52:45,840 --> 01:52:51,870
I had run for three years,
two months, 14 days and 16 hours.

1124
01:53:06,960 --> 01:53:09,110
Quiet. Quiet.
He's going to say something.

1125
01:53:20,360 --> 01:53:22,635
I'm pretty tired.

1126
01:53:24,880 --> 01:53:27,189
Think I'll go home now.

1127
01:53:43,960 --> 01:53:46,394
Now what are we supposed to do?

1128
01:53:47,600 --> 01:53:52,355
And just like that,
my runnin' days was over.

1129
01:53:52,440 --> 01:53:54,590
So I went home to Alabama.

1130
01:53:56,280 --> 01:54:00,432
Moments ago, at 2.25 p.m., as
President Reagan was leaving the...

1131
01:54:02,360 --> 01:54:06,194
...five or six gunshots were fired
by an unknown would-be assassin.

1132
01:54:06,280 --> 01:54:08,475
The President was shot
in the chest...

1133
01:54:08,560 --> 01:54:10,312
I picked up the mail.

1134
01:54:10,400 --> 01:54:14,837
And one day, out of the blue clear
sky, I got a letter from Jenny

1135
01:54:14,920 --> 01:54:18,595
wondering if I could come down
to Savannah and see her,

1136
01:54:18,680 --> 01:54:20,671
and that's what I'm doing here.

1137
01:54:21,960 --> 01:54:23,951
She saw me on TV, running.

1138
01:54:24,040 --> 01:54:28,272
I'm supposed to go on the number nine
bus to Richmond Street

1139
01:54:28,360 --> 01:54:34,959
and get off and go one block left
to 1947 Henry Street, apartment 4.

1140
01:54:35,040 --> 01:54:38,396
Why, you don't need to take a bus.

1141
01:54:38,480 --> 01:54:43,315
Henry Street is just five
or six blocks down that way.

1142
01:54:44,240 --> 01:54:47,073
- Down that way?
- Down that way.

1143
01:54:48,840 --> 01:54:51,195
It was nice talking to you.

1144
01:54:53,400 --> 01:54:55,709
I hope everything works out for you!

1145
01:55:06,680 --> 01:55:11,196
- How you doin'? Come in! Come in!
- I got your letter.

1146
01:55:11,280 --> 01:55:17,037
- I was wondering about that.
- This your house?

1147
01:55:17,120 --> 01:55:20,078
Yeah. It's messy right now.
I just got off work.

1148
01:55:20,160 --> 01:55:23,835
It's nice. You got air conditioning.

1149
01:55:29,720 --> 01:55:32,951
- Thank you.
- I ate some.

1150
01:55:34,920 --> 01:55:40,790
I kept a scrapbook of your clippings,
and everything. There you are.

1151
01:55:42,560 --> 01:55:44,471
And this, I got you running.

1152
01:55:46,760 --> 01:55:51,311
I ran a long way. It's a long time.

1153
01:55:53,680 --> 01:55:55,716
And there...

1154
01:56:01,360 --> 01:56:04,830
Listen, Forrest,
I don't know how to say this.

1155
01:56:07,080 --> 01:56:12,518
I just I want to apologise
for anything that I ever did to you

1156
01:56:12,600 --> 01:56:16,434
'cause I was messed up
for a long time, and...

1157
01:56:19,880 --> 01:56:22,599
- Hi.
- Hey, you.

1158
01:56:22,680 --> 01:56:25,638
- This is an old friend from Alabama.
- How do you do?

1159
01:56:25,800 --> 01:56:29,110
Next week my schedule changes,
so I can...

1160
01:56:29,200 --> 01:56:31,395
No problem. Got to go.
I'm double-parked.

1161
01:56:31,480 --> 01:56:33,277
OK. Thanks.

1162
01:56:34,960 --> 01:56:38,669
This is my very good friend Mr Gump.
Can you say hi?

1163
01:56:38,760 --> 01:56:41,115
- Hello, Mr Gump.
- Hello.

1164
01:56:41,200 --> 01:56:45,079
- Can I go watch TV now?
- Yes. Just keep it low.

1165
01:56:47,200 --> 01:56:50,272
- You're a mama, Jenny.
- I'm a mama.

1166
01:56:53,480 --> 01:56:57,155
- His name's Forrest.
- Like me!

1167
01:56:59,360 --> 01:57:04,036
- I named him after his daddy.
- He got a daddy named Forrest, too?

1168
01:57:05,600 --> 01:57:07,955
You're his daddy, Forrest.

1169
01:57:23,960 --> 01:57:27,316
Forrest, look at me.
Look at me, Forrest.

1170
01:57:28,600 --> 01:57:34,277
There's nothing you need to do.
You didn't do anything wrong. OK?

1171
01:57:38,680 --> 01:57:40,432
Isn't he beautiful?

1172
01:57:41,680 --> 01:57:45,673
He's the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

1173
01:57:48,440 --> 01:57:50,192
But...

1174
01:57:53,200 --> 01:57:55,316
Is he smart? Can he...

1175
01:57:55,400 --> 01:57:59,791
He's very smart. He's one
of the smartest in his class.

1176
01:58:07,920 --> 01:58:10,593
Yeah, it's OK. Go talk to him.

1177
01:58:19,440 --> 01:58:22,876
- What are you watching?
- Bert and Ernie.

1178
01:58:44,400 --> 01:58:48,678
Forrest, I'm sick.

1179
01:58:51,120 --> 01:58:54,476
What, do you have
a cough due to a cold?

1180
01:58:54,560 --> 01:58:59,634
I have some virus, and the doctors,
they don't know what it is,

1181
01:58:59,720 --> 01:59:02,757
and there isn't
anything they can do about it.

1182
01:59:07,400 --> 01:59:09,834
You could come home with me.

1183
01:59:12,200 --> 01:59:17,149
You and little Forrest could
come stay at my house in Greenbow.

1184
01:59:20,440 --> 01:59:23,398
I'll take care of you if you're sick.

1185
01:59:24,840 --> 01:59:27,513
Would you marry me, Forrest?

1186
01:59:32,600 --> 01:59:33,953
OK.

1187
01:59:35,600 --> 01:59:37,079
Please take your seats.

1188
01:59:40,400 --> 01:59:43,312
Forrest? It's time to start.

1189
02:00:01,320 --> 02:00:04,551
Hi. Your tie.

1190
02:00:16,960 --> 02:00:19,155
Lieutenant Dan.

1191
02:00:33,320 --> 02:00:37,199
- Lieutenant Dan.
- Hello, Forrest.

1192
02:00:37,560 --> 02:00:41,235
You got new legs. New legs!

1193
02:00:42,480 --> 02:00:46,109
Yeah. I got new legs. Custom-made.

1194
02:00:46,200 --> 02:00:50,352
Titanium alloy. It's what they use
on the space shuttle.

1195
02:00:53,600 --> 02:00:55,556
Magic legs.

1196
02:00:57,320 --> 02:01:01,632
This is my fiancée, Susan.

1197
02:01:04,000 --> 02:01:08,551
- Lieutenant Dan.
- Hi, Forrest.

1198
02:01:08,640 --> 02:01:15,557
- Lieutenant Dan, this is my Jenny.
- Hi. It's nice to meet you finally.

1199
02:01:25,680 --> 02:01:29,593
Do you, Forrest, take Jenny
to be your wife?

1200
02:01:31,240 --> 02:01:35,233
Do you, Jenny,
take Forrest to be your husband?

1201
02:01:36,800 --> 02:01:40,076
And so I pronounce you man and wife.

1202
02:02:09,600 --> 02:02:12,433
- Hey.
- Hi.

1203
02:02:30,720 --> 02:02:33,234
Were you scared in Vietnam?

1204
02:02:34,520 --> 02:02:38,877
Yes. Well, I don't know.

1205
02:02:39,960 --> 02:02:45,239
Sometimes it would stop raining long
enough for the stars to come out.

1206
02:02:47,960 --> 02:02:49,837
And then it was nice.

1207
02:02:53,080 --> 02:02:57,392
It was like just before the sun
goes to bed down on the bayou.

1208
02:02:57,480 --> 02:03:02,190
There was always
a million sparkles on the water.

1209
02:03:03,760 --> 02:03:07,355
Like that mountain lake.
It was so clear, Jenny,

1210
02:03:07,440 --> 02:03:12,594
it looked like there were two skies
one on top of the other.

1211
02:03:14,160 --> 02:03:17,470
And then in the desert,
when the sun comes up,

1212
02:03:20,320 --> 02:03:26,509
I couldn't tell where heaven stopped
and the earth began.

1213
02:03:27,880 --> 02:03:30,075
It was so beautiful.

1214
02:03:34,120 --> 02:03:36,918
I wish I could've been there
with you.

1215
02:03:40,040 --> 02:03:41,951
You were.

1216
02:03:51,680 --> 02:03:53,432
I love you.

1217
02:03:57,280 --> 02:04:00,317
You died on a Saturday morning.

1218
02:04:02,080 --> 02:04:06,073
And I had you placed
here under our tree.

1219
02:04:10,320 --> 02:04:15,838
And I had that house of your father's
bulldozed to the ground.

1220
02:04:19,480 --> 02:04:26,397
Mama always said
that dyin' was a part of life.

1221
02:04:29,520 --> 02:04:31,670
I sure wish it wasn't.

1222
02:04:34,480 --> 02:04:38,519
Little Forrest is doing just fine.

1223
02:04:41,400 --> 02:04:43,868
About to start school again soon,

1224
02:04:44,840 --> 02:04:48,992
and I make his breakfast,
lunch, and dinner every day.

1225
02:04:50,760 --> 02:04:56,710
I make sure he combs his hair
and brushes his teeth every day.

1226
02:04:59,240 --> 02:05:05,110
Teaching him how to play ping-pong.
He's really good.

1227
02:05:05,200 --> 02:05:07,156
Forrest, you go.

1228
02:05:11,720 --> 02:05:13,836
We fish a lot.

1229
02:05:17,040 --> 02:05:20,715
And every night, we read a book.
He's so smart, Jenny.

1230
02:05:23,000 --> 02:05:27,835
You'd be so proud of him. I am.

1231
02:05:29,160 --> 02:05:32,118
He wrote you a letter.

1232
02:05:33,600 --> 02:05:35,636
And he says I can't read it.

1233
02:05:35,720 --> 02:05:39,599
I'm not supposed to,
so I'll just leave it here for you.

1234
02:06:01,400 --> 02:06:07,236
I don't know if mama was right
or if it's Lieutenant Dan.

1235
02:06:08,120 --> 02:06:14,719
I don't know if
we each have a destiny,

1236
02:06:14,800 --> 02:06:21,319
or if we're all just floating around
accidental-like on a breeze.

1237
02:06:25,560 --> 02:06:30,350
But I think maybe it's both.

1238
02:06:34,960 --> 02:06:38,111
Maybe both is happening
at the same time.

1239
02:06:43,560 --> 02:06:45,437
But I miss you, Jenny.

1240
02:06:51,600 --> 02:06:56,116
If there's anything you need,
I won't be far away.

1241
02:07:29,600 --> 02:07:33,275
Here's your bus. OK.

1242
02:07:35,280 --> 02:07:37,191
I know this.

1243
02:07:37,280 --> 02:07:39,953
I'm gonna share that for
show-and-tell

1244
02:07:40,040 --> 02:07:42,679
because Grandma
used to read it to you.

1245
02:07:42,760 --> 02:07:44,716
My favourite book.

1246
02:07:51,600 --> 02:07:53,795
Here you go.

1247
02:08:00,520 --> 02:08:01,919
Don't...

1248
02:08:04,000 --> 02:08:08,994
- I want to tell you I love you.
- I love you, too, Daddy.

1249
02:08:09,080 --> 02:08:12,152
I'll be right here when you get back.

1250
02:08:16,480 --> 02:08:20,712
You understand this is
the bus to school, don't you?

1251
02:08:20,800 --> 02:08:25,430
Of course, and you're Dorothy Harris,
and I'm Forrest Gump.


